                    "company": "University of Antwerp",
                    "description": "I examine the toxicity of perfluoroalkyl substances (PFASs) to terrestrial invertebrates and songbirds. I analyze these effects at different levels of biological organization. \n\nDuring this research, I developed a new analytical method (using ultraperformance liquid chromatography-mass spectrometry (UPLC-MS) for the chemical extraction of PFASs from environmental matrices. I analyzed the concentrations of PFASs in soil, isopods, great tits (Parus major) and blue tits (Cyanistes caeruleus) at different locations near a fluorochemical plant in Antwerp, Belgium. I assessed the effects of PFASs pollution on reproduction of the birds, as well as multiple indicators of biological condition of birds and isopods. And finally, I examined the role of physicochemical properties, such as grain size or organic carbon content, of the soil on the bioavailability of PFASs to animals.",
